    <h1 id="module-overview">Module overview</h1>
<h2 id="available-protocols">Available Protocols</h2>
<p>This module outlines the protocol for recording fire severity within
the plot. The protocol involves recording the cover and height of fire
severity attributes from the ground to the canopy at 404
point-intercepts along four 100 m transects within the plot as well as
trunk char height at four locations within the plot.</p>
<p>The protocol includes the instructions and procedures for: setting up
four 100 m transects (2 x N/S and 2 x E/W; see <a href="#figure-1">Figure 1</a>); recording
point-intercept fire severity data at 1 m intervals along the four
transects (for a total of 404 point-intercepts); recording trunk char
height from the four locations where the four transects intersect; and
entering the data directly into the Monitor app.</p>
<p>The guidelines provide further information regarding: workflow
efficiency; the rules for determining a 'hit’; using a densitometer to
view canopy intercepts; when to apply <em>in canopy sky</em> (ICS); and
taking trunk char height measurements.</p>
<h2 id="relationship-to-other-modules">Relationship to other
modules</h2>
<h3 id="mandatory-related-modules">Mandatory related modules</h3>
<h4 class="unnumbered" id="complete-before-the-fire-severity-module">Complete before the Fire
Severity Module</h4>
<ul>
<li><p><a href="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/d15d05db-5007-411e-b257-105ef4f76821">Plot Selection and Layout Module</a> – The point-intercept transect
grid is aligned to the plot defined boundaries.</p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/2b5c2281-e0f4-4ef5-8ae0-8ae745af9a7e">Floristics Module</a> – This module provides the flora
species identifications/assigned field names and growth forms to be used
in the collection of species data (if using the enhanced Cover
protocol).</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 class="unnumbered" id="complete-concurrently-with-the-fire-severity-module">Complete
concurrently with the Fire Severity Module</h4>
<ul>
<li><p><a href="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/c3403517-fcc6-4389-9c09-f1e1ee8b0f3b">Cover Module</a> – The Fire Severity Module must be undertaken
concurrently using the same transects.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id="optional-complementary-related-modules">Optional complementary
related modules</h3>
<ul>
<li><p><a href="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/4f0f0ca4-d8f7-472d-9203-f46a565ad970">Recruitment Module</a> – Fire mediated regeneration and epicormic
growth can be measured. Both modules can be undertaken concurrently
using the same plot layout.</p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/1ff9e97c-3bdd-44c9-bdd3-401fa31c0b32">Plot Description Module</a> – Fire history (unburnt, recently burnt,
past burn) is recorded in the Plot Description module.</p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/15361f98-7669-410e-9b04-e9be069c7508">Vegetation Mapping Module</a> – Fire history (unburnt, recently
burnt, past burn) is recorded at each vegetation mapping point in the
Vegetation Mapping Module.</p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/0d8b47b4-1ca8-4c76-8329-0eb781a823a2">Coarse Woody Debris Module</a> – Both modules can be undertaken
concurrently using the same plot layout.</p></li>
</ul>"""^^rdf:HTML ;
